[{"type":"{{","value":[["pagebanner"],["Berwick upon Tweed banner bridges.JPG"],["caption=Royal Tweed Bridge and Old Bridge from Royal Border Bridge"]]},"\n",{"type":"'''","value":["Berwick-upon-Tweed"]}," is a historic walled town in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Northumberland"]]},". It is the most northerly town in England,just 2 1\/2 miles from the border and its strategic location means that it has changed hands following wars between England and Scotland a total of nine times. Berwick is pronounced 'Berrick'.\n\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Image:Berwick bridges.jpg"],["thumb"],["300px"],["Berwick bridges."]]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get in"]},"\n\nBerwick has its own train station, and is about 45 mins from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Edinburgh"]]}," or 3 hours 45 mins from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["London"]]}," on the East Coast Mainline.\n\nBuses run from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Newcastle upon Tyne"],["Newcastle"]]},". However, the majority of visitors will come from the A1 trunk road from England into Scotland. The old A1 ran into the town, but the modern road bypasses the town to the west.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get around"]},"\nBerwick is a beautiful town to walk around. There is no necessity to use the bus as most attractions are located within a small radius.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["See"]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Image:Berwick castle walls.jpg"],["thumb"],["300px"],["Berwick castle walls."]]},"\n\n",{"type":"*","value":[" The town is surrounded by historic walled ramparts, constructed during times of war between England and Scotland."]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Berwick Barracks and Main Guard"],["alt="],["url=http:\/\/www.english-heritage.org.uk\/daysout\/properties\/berwick-upon-tweed-barracks-and-main-guard\/"],["email="],["address=Parade, TD15 1DF"],["lat=55.770995"],["long=-2.001111"],["directions="],["phone=+44 1289 304493"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price=adults £4.00, children £2.4